      "name": "Will selling my Brisbane home affect my Age Pension?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Your principal home is an exempt asset for the Centrelink assets test. The moment you sell, the cash proceeds become a counted asset, and that can reduce or cancel your Age Pension. Centrelink applies a temporary exemption to the portion of proceeds you genuinely intend to use to buy or build a new home, generally for up to 24 months, but the deeming rules still apply to that money during the exemption period. The practical effect for many downsizers in Brisbane's inner east is that net surplus cash from a downsize sits above the assets test thresholds and changes their pension entitlement."
      }
    },
